{
  "texts": [
    "This approach not only improved multiscale vehicle object detection performance but also enhanced robustness in detecting small and heavily occluded objects.Reference [42] improved the multiscale predictive network model based on actual traffic conditions and efficiency requirements, which resulted in improved detection accuracy and speed.",
    "They achieved this by adding scale prediction layers to enhance the detection accuracy of large vehicles and by using an improved k-means++ algorithm for anchor box dimension clustering to boost detection speed and effectiveness.",
    "The results showed that the F-yolov3 model outperforms the traditional YOLOv3 algorithm in terms of accuracy mapping and speed.",
    "Reference [43] introduced lightweight C3Ghost and Ghost modules into the necking network of YOLOV5 to achieve model compression while maintaining detection accuracy and speed.",
    "They added a Convolutional Block Attention Module (CBAM) to the network to select critical information and suppress non-critical information for the vehicle detection task, which ultimately improved the detection accuracy."
  ]
}